 that was noticed during implementing something, we would track it. can yuo find that system and then explain it to me'), (134,17,'2026-06-14 13:02:54','fbe732fc-9437-4df1-970a-62c38004fe6d','on_demand','AT some point I think we worked on a system where if there was some architectural gap or something like that was noticed during implementing something, we would track it. can yuo find that system and ',NULL,'8857a6651d305b9b6dcdcd27d04d86a6c5145727',0,NULL,'0.1.0','AT some point I think we worked on a system where if there was some architectural gap or something like that was noticed during implementing something, we would track it. can yuo find that system and then explain it to me'), (135,7,'2026-06-14 13:02:56','fbe732fc-9437-4df1-970a-62c38004fe6d','on_demand','AT some point I think we worked on a system where if there was some architectural gap or something like that was noticed during implementing something, we would track it. can yuo find that system and ',NULL,'8857a6651d305b9b6dcdcd27d04d86a6c5145727',0,NULL,'0.1.0','AT some point I think we worked on a system where if there was some architectural gap or something like that was noticed during implementing something, we would track it. can yuo find that system and then explain it to me'), (136,13,'2026-06-14 13:10:22','fbe732fc-9437-4df1-970a-62c38004fe6d','on_demand','dispatch has autonmous triage? So it does the work in the shelf before the next large chunk of work?',NULL,'8857a6651d305b9b6dcdcd27d04d86a6c5145727',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','dispatch has autonmous triage? So it does the work in the shelf before the next large chunk of work?'), (137,12,'2026-06-14 13:10:24','fbe732fc-9437-4df1-970a-62c38004fe6d','on_demand','dispatch has autonmous triage? So it does the work in the shelf before the next large chunk of work?',NULL,'8857a6651d305b9b6dcdcd27d04d86a6c5145727',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','dispatch has autonmous triage? So it does the work in the shelf before the next large chunk of work?'), (138,17,'2026-06-14 13:21:37','7012d564-ef0f-4469-bc0a-018f492c061d','on_demand','Are these takeaways different from the line-items in monitions? These are the ones that are produced at end of session mine, right?',NULL,'8857a6651d305b9b6dcdcd27d04d86a6c5145727',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','Are these takeaways different from the line-items in monitions? These are the ones that are produced at end of session mine, right?'), (139,5,'2026-06-14 13:33:13','7012d564-ef0f-4469-bc0a-018f492c061d','edit_path','.claude/skills/mine-session/SKILL.md',NULL,'8857a6651d305b9b6dcdcd27d04d86a6c5145727',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','6. **Routing a domain-free lesson — the incubator is the upstream, so don\'t queue\n   it.** A `--mirror candidate` row waits for a sweep that pulls it *up*; CMS has no\n   upstream. Decide now instead: if the lesson would help a *generated* project,\n   propose it straight into `payload/lessons.md.template` (a tier-0 block) through\n   the consent gate; if it only applies to building the incubator or its modules,\n   leave it a local row (`mirror none`, the default). Reserve `--mirror candidate`\n   for instantiated downstream projects, where the upstream is real.'), (140,6,'2026-06-14 13:33:14','7012d564-ef0f-4469-bc0a-018f492c061d','edit_path','.claude/skills/mine-session/SKILL.md',NULL,'8857a6651d305b9b6dcdcd27d04d86a6c5145727',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','6. **Routing a domain-free lesson — the incubator is the upstream, so don\'t queue\n   it.** A `--mirror candidate` row waits for a sweep that pulls it *up*; CMS has no\n   upstream. Decide now instead: if the lesson would help a *generated* project,\n   propose it straight into `payload/lessons.md.template` (a tier-0 block) through\n   the consent gate; if it only applies to building the incubator or its modules,\n   leave it a local row (`mirror none`, the default). Reserve `--mirror candidate`\n   for instantiated downstream projects, where the upstream is real.'), (141,8,'2026-06-14 13:37:28','fbe732fc-9437-4df1-970a-62c38004fe6d','edit_path','payload/skills/dispatch/SKILL.md','noise','7c54f8152cec8938e4609d25176a5c7bb32c5ae7',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','   names something the data model lacks (a status that isn\'t a status), surface the\n   mismatch first rather than silently translating it. Before report-first, if\n   `docs/debt.md` exists, grep it for the files this phase touches; surface any hits\n   with a fold-in / sibling / parked call (fold in only within budget).'), (142,9,'2026-06-14 13:37:31','fbe732fc-9437-4df1-970a-62c38004fe6d','edit_path','method/dispatch.md','helpful','7c54f8152cec8938e4609d25176a5c7bb32c5ae7',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','discoveries. Lessons land at the narrowest scope that will fire.\n\n**Debt relevance gate.** Between reading a bucket\'s touchpoints and reporting, grep\n`docs/debt.md` for those same paths: a match is debt in a file you\'re about to open\nanyway, so its fix is nearly free. Surface hits in report-first with a fold-in /\nsibling-bucket / leave-parked call (fold in only within the bucket\'s budget). This is\nthe capture trigger\'s mirror — capture parks debt while the function is open; the gate\nspends it when the function reopens. Distinct from the autonomous-triage sweep: the\nsweep drains the whole shelf by *safety* on demand; the gate drains by *relevance*,\ninline.\n\nThe generator prompt that produces these files carries its own Updates section —'), (143,15,'2026-06-14 13:46:07','7012d564-ef0f-4469-bc0a-018f492c061d','on_demand','shouldn\'t there be another tech-debt specific system that captures this kind of thing? review your own context management systems','helpful','7c54f8152cec8938e4609d25176a5c7bb32c5ae7',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','shouldn\'t there be another tech-debt specific system that captures this kind of thing? review your own context management systems'), (144,3,'2026-06-14 17:11:02','ee2cd166-82ad-4e1e-a965-920ee63a316d','session_start',NULL,NULL,'f7ddab6d1b00b949a81a4c79e55511c7790ebdac