629d5d6','session_start',NULL,NULL,'80d044d3be9c88bc034b16e6bae46781facd055c',0,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0',NULL), (162,9,'2026-06-14 20:24:09','e2f3abf3-d743-4b5f-b1cf-5fad214ea138','edit_path','method/instantiate.md','noise','80d044d3be9c88bc034b16e6bae46781facd055c',0,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','   store, imports the starter lessons as rows, and wires Monition\'s own hooks), then\n   delete `lessons.md` — adoption is one-way and the store now owns the rows. Then\n   make the Dolt store enter git as reviewable text, not binaries: add\n   `monition/.dolt/` to `.gitignore`; wire dump regeneration into `.githooks/pre-commit`\n   (`monition dump` → `git add monition/dump.sql`, guarded by `[ -d monition/.dolt ]`,\n   after the linter line); and run `monition dump` once before the step-6 commit so\n   `dump.sql` exists. Git then tracks only the derived `dump.sql`; the binary `.dolt/`\n   stays local with its own dolt history.'), (163,18,'2026-06-14 20:24:40','6bb2ccd0-e8e0-4b06-a627-e34c0629d5d6','on_demand','do the context management systems work when agents are running the tasks? like for example if I automate the workstream such that an agent is doing each bucket, is it running session wrap and session ','helpful','80d044d3be9c88bc034b16e6bae46781facd055c',1,NULL,'0.1.0','do the context management systems work when agents are running the tasks? like for example if I automate the workstream such that an agent is doing each bucket, is it running session wrap and session mine? is the orchestrating architect doing that? isn\'t this a gap?'), (164,19,'2026-06-14 20:24:41','6bb2ccd0-e8e0-4b06-a627-e34c0629d5d6','on_demand','do the context management systems work when agents are running the tasks? like for example if I automate the workstream such that an agent is doing each bucket, is it running session wrap and session ','helpful','80d044d3be9c88bc034b16e6bae46781facd055c',1,NULL,'0.1.0','do the context management systems work when agents are running the tasks? like for example if I automate the workstream such that an agent is doing each bucket, is it running session wrap and session mine? is the orchestrating architect doing that? isn\'t this a gap?'), (165,7,'2026-06-14 20:24:42','6bb2ccd0-e8e0-4b06-a627-e34c0629d5d6','on_demand','do the context management systems work when agents are running the tasks? like for example if I automate the workstream such that an agent is doing each bucket, is it running session wrap and session ','noise','80d044d3be9c88bc034b16e6bae46781facd055c',1,NULL,'0.1.0','do the context management systems work when agents are running the tasks? like for example if I automate the workstream such that an agent is doing each bucket, is it running session wrap and session mine? is the orchestrating architect doing that? isn\'t this a gap?'), (166,15,'2026-06-14 20:24:44','6bb2ccd0-e8e0-4b06-a627-e34c0629d5d6','on_demand','do the context management systems work when agents are running the tasks? like for example if I automate the workstream such that an agent is doing each bucket, is it running session wrap and session ','helpful','80d044d3be9c88bc034b16e6bae46781facd055c',1,NULL,'0.1.0','do the context management systems work when agents are running the tasks? like for example if I automate the workstream such that an agent is doing each bucket, is it running session wrap and session mine? is the orchestrating architect doing that? isn\'t this a gap?'), (167,9,'2026-06-14 22:06:17','6bb2ccd0-e8e0-4b06-a627-e34c0629d5d6','edit_path','method/learning-loop.md',NULL,'80d044d3be9c88bc034b16e6bae46781facd055c',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','- This mining discipline is canonical here; the Monition module\'s mine-session template\n  mirrors the pass (domain-stripped), propagated by `monition sync` — the same channel\n  `lesson-routing.md` uses. Bump and hand off here on any change.\n- **Delegated runs route the end pass through the architect.** When buckets are\n  dispatched to stateless workers, the workers persist per-bucket gotchas to their\n  `Updates` but cannot run the end-of-session pass; the architect runs one run-level mine\n  (and one run-level wrap) over the worker results plus accumulated Updates. See\n  `dispatch.md` §Architect → implementer.'), (168,12,'2026-06-14 22:11:40','6bb2ccd0-e8e0-4b06-a627-e34c0629d5d6','on_demand','I notice that whenever something the system prompt suggests to add something to memory, we should be instead adding it to our own custom context management systems','noise','80d044d3be9c88bc034b16e6bae46781facd055c',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','I notice that whenever something the system prompt suggests to add something to memory, we should be instead adding it to our own custom context management systems'), (169,7,'2026-06-14 22:59:43','e2f3abf3-d743-4b5f-b1cf-5fad214ea138','on_demand','done? do I need session mine/wrap/clear?',NULL,'80d044d3be9c88bc034b16e6bae46781facd055c',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','done? do I need session mine/wrap/clear?'), (170,18,'2026-06-14 22:59:44','e2f3abf3-d743-4b5f-b1cf-5fad214ea138','on_demand','done? do I need session mine/wrap/clear?',NULL,'80d044d3be9c88bc034b16e6bae46781facd055c',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','done? do I need session mine/wrap/clear?'), (171,3,'2026-06-15 01:21:31','4018b369-76a5-4140-aded-e0ecd91d2227','session_start',NULL,'helpful','d37086b81f90b6b670e686301e5f64e2d0dd4bc1',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0',NULL), (172,7,'2026-06-15 01:25:25','4018b369-76a5-4140-aded-e0ecd91d2227','on_demand','You\'ll find your answers in projects\\brain2\\Handoffs\\RCA-handoffs After you create repo move the handoffs from that folder into the repo-specific ones.',NULL,'d37086b81f90b6b670e686301e5f64e2d0dd4bc1',1,'claude-opus-4-8','0.1.0','You\'ll find your answers in projects\\brain2\\Handoffs\\RCA-handoffs After you create repo move the handoffs from that folder into the repo-specific ones.'), (173,20,'2026-06-15 01:25:27','4018b369-76a5-4140-aded-e0ecd91d2227','on_demand','You\'ll find your answers in projects\\brain